WEBVTT

00:06.006 --> 00:08.175
THIS PROGRAM IS LOOSELY
BASED ON ACTUAL EVENTS.

00:08.258 --> 00:11.011
CHARACTERS AND EVENTS WERE
ADAPTED FOR DRAMATIC EFFECT.

00:14.306 --> 00:17.392
In Brazil, people think that being a cop

00:17.476 --> 00:20.521
means invading favelas and
shootouts with drug dealers.

00:23.357 --> 00:26.693
FEDERAL POLICE

00:27.277 --> 00:28.737
That's not being a cop.

00:29.905 --> 00:31.573
That's being a stupid cop.

00:35.369 --> 00:38.705
It's not the violence in favelas
that's fucking up our country.

00:39.998 --> 00:44.586
It's not the lack of education,
broken health system,

00:45.504 --> 00:47.631
public deficit or interest rates.

00:49.841 --> 00:53.136
What's fucking up our country is
the cause of all these things.

00:59.643 --> 01:01.311
Twenty years serving the police.

01:02.396 --> 01:03.730
I've never been corrupted.

01:04.147 --> 01:05.649
Never invaded a single favela.

01:08.026 --> 01:09.319
Never been called a hero.

01:15.534 --> 01:17.452
But you know what I've found out?

01:21.081 --> 01:24.042
What's really fucking up
Brazilian people's lives.

01:24.626 --> 01:25.794
It's like a cancer.

01:28.714 --> 01:30.048
A cancer, you know?

01:32.175 --> 01:34.469
If we don't strike at the
root of the problem,

01:36.263 --> 01:37.681
the shit will spread.

01:38.557 --> 01:39.891
Ten B.

01:40.392 --> 01:42.394
Ten billion dollars.

01:42.477 --> 01:44.521
Nineteen bank accounts. I traced four.

01:44.604 --> 01:46.398
Ten billion at the least.

01:47.107 --> 01:48.734
What does he do for a living?

01:50.736 --> 01:51.945
He sells fried pastries.

01:52.821 --> 01:55.449
He used to sell sfihas at a stoplight.

01:55.907 --> 01:57.367
He was Ruffo's classmate.

01:57.451 --> 01:59.786
Unfortunately I went to
school with that prick.

01:59.870 --> 02:02.414
He started smuggling goods
at Friendship Bridge,

02:02.497 --> 02:03.874
then became a drug runner.

02:03.957 --> 02:06.710
But he made a name for himself
with money laundering.

02:06.793 --> 02:08.794
- Want me to get that?
- No, I got it.

02:09.253 --> 02:10.172
Hey, baby.

02:11.256 --> 02:12.132
Regina?

02:12.924 --> 02:14.092
Regina?

02:22.934 --> 02:24.645
Must be my daughter playing.

02:26.938 --> 02:28.857
Twenty years serving the police.

02:30.359 --> 02:33.153
Enough to buy a used car for my wife...

02:33.695 --> 02:36.740
and a ranch in Paraná to
secure my daughter's future.

02:44.706 --> 02:46.458
Ten... billion?

02:46.541 --> 02:49.294
Nice chunk of change, right?
Upper middle class.

02:49.378 --> 02:55.133
More than all drug trafficking
and smuggling in Brazil.

02:55.717 --> 02:57.260
Where's that money coming from?

02:57.636 --> 02:59.388
That's what I plan to find out.

02:59.471 --> 03:00.764
I started the investigation,

03:00.847 --> 03:04.267
but a federal officer can't get
access to offshore accounts.

03:04.351 --> 03:06.853
I took the case to the
Public Prosecutor's Office.

03:07.187 --> 03:08.605
Cláudio and Dimas.

03:08.814 --> 03:11.691
The Public Prosecutor's
Office was my only way in.

03:11.817 --> 03:15.237
If you would be kind enough to
lift Ibrahim's bank secrecy,

03:15.320 --> 03:16.696
this could be a very good day.

03:16.780 --> 03:18.031
Fettucine's on me.

03:19.533 --> 03:20.951
For you, not him.

03:22.160 --> 03:24.287
No one fights a cancer
and walks away unharmed.

03:24.371 --> 03:25.414
No one.

03:25.497 --> 03:27.332
Those pencil-pushers laughed at me.

03:27.707 --> 03:28.708
Cláudio and Dimas.

03:28.792 --> 03:30.710
Today they're considered heroes.

03:31.837 --> 03:34.631
But in the beginning, they
treated me like a lunatic.

03:35.674 --> 03:40.512
- Where did you find this?
- These bank statements...

03:41.221 --> 03:44.349
He's a real son of a bitch. He
shreds and dumps everything.

03:44.933 --> 03:46.476
So I piece it all together.

03:46.560 --> 03:49.938
It's a pain in the ass because
my fingers get sticky.

03:50.564 --> 03:54.025
You salvaged all of this from the trash?

03:54.109 --> 03:55.152
From the trash, yeah.

03:56.737 --> 03:58.989
Your buddy prints out these statements

03:59.072 --> 04:01.658
just to keep you up all night
gluing scraps together.

04:02.242 --> 04:04.369
Ruffo, I can't build a case on this.

04:04.453 --> 04:06.997
And no judge would accept
trash as evidence.

